author: COMSOL
description: This is a benchmark case for turbulent compressible flow in a 2D converging-diverging nozzle (Sajben diffuser). The flow enters the diffuser at Ma = 0.46, accelerates through the converging part, and reaches sonic conditions at the nozzle throat. The supersonic flow is terminated by a shock in the diverging part. The stationary positions of the shock wave are computed for two different outlet pressure values.
